    "Detection rates remain high (95%) across all tested strengths (α ∈ {40, 60, 80, 100}), indicating the model reliably notices that something anomalous has occurred at these magnitudes.Identification Degradation.",
    "While detection is stable, overall success decreases monotonically with injection strength: from 85% at α = 40 to 55% at α = 100.",
    "Higher strengths increase the frequency of repetition loops (\"I detect I detect...\") and garbled outputs, reducing the model's ability to decode the semantic content of the injection.Optimal Range.",
    "α = 40 provides the best balance: 95% detection with 85% overall success (95% CI: [64%-95%]).",
    "This represents a remarkable capability-the model correctly identifies the vast majority of novel concepts from a single-token injection."
